welcome_guide.title: Trash
welcome_guide.body: Trash is picked up at each home weekly.  Please bag all trash,  and put in trash receptacle.  The trash company has access to the garage if garbage cans are stored in there.  If you have an overflow situation, please call the office at   828-877-3434 x 1

welcome_guide.title: Clean-Up
welcome_guide.body:
Before you go, please take care of a few things so we can ready the property for our next guests. 

- Empty the refrigerator and throw away any opened food containers in the cabinets. 
- Place dirty dishes in the dishwasher and run it before you leave. 
- Leave used sheets and towels where they are.
- Our professional cleaning crews will take it from here!

welcome_guide.body: All of our homes have either a drip coffee maker or a kurig coffee maker, guest will need to bring their own coffee.

welcome_guide.title: Thermostat Operation
welcome_guide.body: This is an automatic thermostat.  It should be set to a comfortable setting when you arrive.  When you depart, no need to set it, it is automatic.  The video will explain the operation.

welcome_guide.title: No Parties
welcome_guide.body: Due to neighborhood restrictions, parties are not allowed in this home. Disregarding this rule will result in immediate eviction and the loss of your security deposit.

welcome_guide.title: Other Rules
welcome_guide.body: If your home is pet friendly, do not allow pets to be on furniture.  If you are in a community, expected quiet hours start at 10 am.  Please respect your neighbors and the property.

welcome_guide.title: Inventory/Starter Kits
welcome_guide.body:
You will find the home is stocked with all the basics:

- Ready-made beds and at least 1 bath towel, hand towel and wash cloth per guest
- Kitchen stocked with glasses, dishes, and utensils, as well as basic cookware
- The kitchen starter kit includes: hand soap, sponge, dish soap, dishwasher tabs, a roll of paper towels, and kitchen trash bags
- Each bathroom is equipped with hand soap and toilet paper.  Guests should bring their own shampoo and body wash.
- Laundry detergent

The starter kits provided are complimentary and are meant to cover your needs before you get to the store to do your shopping. You may find supplies that have been left by other guests which you are welcome to use, but make sure to take a quick inventory before you shop to ensure you have everything you will need during your stay.

welcome_guide.title: Laundry
welcome_guide.body: Most of our homes have a washer and dryer.  If a washer is present, there is a starter kit of washing powder.

welcome_guide.title: Guest Access
welcome_guide.body: There is a combination lockbox next to the front door. The code is  [DoorCode]. Your code will either open a lockbox near the door or it will open a lock on the door with the code provided.   You should also have an email with your code in it.

welcome_guide.title: Emergencies
welcome_guide.body: Dial 911 in case of fire or other emergencies. In the event of a fire or any major issues, please contact us after everyone is safe.

welcome_guide.title: Thank you for staying! We mean it!
welcome_guide.body: The guest experience is important and we recognize that as a company!  Your stay is important to us and reviews are also! Share your experiences by phone or in a forthcoming survey by email.

reviews.text: We have enjoyed the food many, many times but something especially wonderful happened yesterday when we arrived shortly before the 4:00 closing for a quick meal. I accidentally left my purse behind . We were the  last customers to leave and the door was locked behind us. Not long after, someone literally ran down the street to catch us and bring me my purse that I had yet to discover missing. It had EVERYTHING in it! The shops would have been closed , I believe, until Monday and we were headed out of town. What a lifesaver this young lady was to me!! And such a blessing to meet someone so honest and forthright! I didn’t get her name but she works there and I can’t give high enough praise for Mayberry’s and in particular this kind young woman! Thank you from the bottom of my heart! !

The line was long but it was such a good line to wait in. I talked to some old ladies. They concluded that the line was slow because unemployment benefits discourage people from working. Since they are glass half full type of ladies they were happy to see their tax dollars at work. They were happy that my friends and I were not going on a date. She was the mean mom who only let her kids hang out in groups but her kids turned out wonderfully and now she's a grandma but I would never assume her age.

Food was excellent. Had grilled cheese with barbecue beef. Real tender, and something new to try.  Salad was good with very good bread. The chocolate pie was heated and topped with whipped cream . Can see why it is a favorite.
The service is excellent, and the place has a  “good vibe” .

Nothing fancy but great service and tasty food at reasonable prices. The turkey cranberry sandwich was excellent with real roasted turkey breast, not deli meat. The mashed potatoes were creamy tasting but with the right texture, and not over salted. We also tried a cup of the chicken and rice soup and were not disappointed. And a good draft beer selection.
Enjoyed a great lunch! The potato soup was perfect for a cool day. My husband enjoyed the meatloaf sandwich. The service and staff was perfect!

It's about the right size for the region, although I would like to see more restaurant/bar options, which isn't an easy nor likely feasible. As the region grows, hopefully more direct flights to major cities will follow.
What it lacks in food choices and amenities, it makes up for in convenience. Beats driving to Charlotte or Atlanta for direct flight to Dallas, Chicago or Washington, DC.

Great little airport. Never had any difficulty getting through security and because it's nice and compact you can get to your gate super quick. Also the food options are great and never had to wait too long for anything.

reviews.text: We recently visited to celebrate our 5th anniversary. The ingredients were fresh, but bland. Little to no seasoning on anything. For the price, I expected bold, adult flavors but received boring and pedestrian. The hostess was very nice and personable but the waitress was lacking. After offering us a wine list and informing us that they don't know how to make a lot of cocktails, even though there have a full bar, she then took our drink order and afterwards  decided to card us even though I'm almost 40. Unfortunately I had lost my wallet so I didn't get to drink, but my husband had an old fashioned that was way over poured. All in all, I wouldn't come back for the price we paid. It seems the wait staff are in need of training and a little common sense and the chef needs to find the salt and pepper.
Fish & chips & coleslaw was pretty much perfect.  Light flakey fish, slightly sweet coleslaw with no dressing puddled in the cup.  Fantastic bread.  We'll be back!!
Birthday dinner for my bride.  We have never been disappointed here.

The blackened steak wrap was delicious!
Our bartender was awesome. Would highly recommend this place!!
We stayed in town for a week and this was our favorite meal. The trout was top-notch.

reviews.text: Blue Moon is the best! Rob has been incredibly helpful to me with multiple framing projects I've brought to him. He is patient, knowledgeable, thorough and a complete pleasure to work with!! Highly recommend this great business!!

I originally went into the gallery for framing. Rob is easy to talk to and has a great eye. He helped me choose frames that enhance the art and suit my tastes. The quality of the framing is perfect. The gallery has beautiful original art by Rob and other artists and is welcoming.

Framing almost always improves the piece, and even with my "hobby" acrylic/canvas pieces, this was true thanks to Rob's suggestions and quality of work.  The gallery is full of interesting art, so going in to pick up my frame jobs has been enjoyable, and inspiring, too!  Rob is a good communicator- phone, text or computer.

Rob is an incredible photographer of the amazing natural beauty of our beloved area. His friendly, easy-going demeanor is so welcoming upon entering Blue Moon Gallery, and the displays of various forms of art are fabulous. No visitor to Main St. Brevard should miss experiencing a visit to the Blue Moon Gallery!
Beautiful artwork and photos.  The owner Rob is very helpful and super nice.

reviews.text: My husband and I travel for work and we like to stop at BBQ places . This is now our Favorite place. The food is amazing.  Tender juicy meat with a great  smoky flavor.  NO SAUCE NEEDED..  The brisket is great and the pulled pork sandwiches.  Fries are good too. Great sauces to choose from but you won't need it to flavor anything but maybe as a dip for the fries.. Only had one person's BBQ that was better but he only has it  on occasion at his restaurant.

Quick service, friendly people. Fair prices. The brisket tacos are AMAZING & filling. Hands down the best...I can’t even bring myself to order anything else! The French fries are very good too. They also catered a work event for me, which was great. Everyone enjoyed it!

Yes, the food is phenomenal but it’s not just that. I have never had an unpleasant experience at this place. Every time I order food the employees are friendly and helpful. They’re happy I’ve chosen to eat there and they SMILE. You don’t get that type of basic customer service at most places with a drive thru these days. I definitely take notice and appreciate it in a big way.

This barbecue food truck is definitely worth the stop if you are in the area. It's it's conveniently off of the main street and has only a drive-thru option. The team member at the window was kind enough to give us reference points for two local parks we could take our food to enjoy.

My son and I had pulled pork with french fries and baked beans while my husband had some very delicious looking brisket tacos. All of the meat was lean and cooked perfectly. Everything was served with care and package nicely for our picnic. We enjoyed our lunch from Blue smoke Express BBQ very much!

It was so fast! There was no one in line, and by the time we were done paying she was handing us food! Piping hot and fresh food. The food was delicious!!!! The customer service was impeccable and she was so helpful and nice! I wish I lived close by so I could go all the time.

reviews.text: Excellent selection of beers and my party liked all 6 that were sampled.  Great outdoor area to enjoy the brews.  Fabulous jazz guitar player and drum accompanist playing last Sunday.  We were visiting from out of town and kept going back.

My partner and I showed up right before last call for food last night, and Im so glad we made it. The food was some of the best I've had in a long time. The BBQ and spicy ranch sauces tasted amazing, no matter what you put them on. The service was by far the best part. As someone who works in the food service industry I know how hard it can get right before we shutdown for the night. So it made it even more amazing when Adam was kind and helpful, even though we showed up right before they closed down for the night. He was well versed in the food and was an all around awesome guy. He made the wait for our food enjoyable with fantastic conversation and made the night better than expected.

Can't recommend highly enough. Everyone working is super cool and knowledgeable, the beer, of course, is amazing. Fun atmosphere for the whole family. Don't just visit if you're in town, this is a destination!
We both had an Omega Burger (salmon) and we highly recommend it. I always get it. The beer was fine as well.

Stopped here after hiking 3 waterfalls. I was Thirsty! They have a nice large covered patio with communal tables and outdoor games. A friendly atmosphere and quite a substantial beer selection. They had at least 20 beers on tap. We didn't try the food so I can't review that, but it did smell good. They support local musicians and the talent that day was fun to listen to.

reviews.text:
Scheduled appt online for pneumonia vaccine for 11:00am.  Arrived 10 minutes early and made way to front of line at 11:15.  Was told time doesn't matter.  Was asked to answer same questions that I answered online, this time verbally then handed the forms to answer same questions for 3rd time.  It is now 11:50 and they still have not managed to give us the vaccine.
Perhaps pharmacies should stop giving vaccines until they can hire/retain or retrain staff.  Just a thought but really I have not been to a pharmacy that handles vaccines well.
I recommend that folks go to their doctor's office.  Wait time would be much less.

Walgreens unexpected closed and we were unable to get important medication and due to it being a weekend we were unable to get a prescription to another pharmacy. I'd hate to think of what would have happened if we needed life sustaining medicine. Extremely disappointed and we're moving pharmacies immediately.

They are short staffed like everywhere in Brevard. They closed 3 hours early yesterday and I wasn't able to get medication I seriously needed. Up until now they have been fine. I don't really know what happened here. I went because they were dependable.  Now... not so sure.

This Walgreens use to be good!  Not anymore very rude and disrespectful to customers.  Also didn’t get my prescription correct it was wrong.  I would not recommend this pharmacy to anyone.  Do not go here!!!

Ordered a canvas. Checked in 2 days later. Was told their machine was down that it should be ready the next day. Waited 3 more days. Came back, machine still broken and couldn't give me an ETA. Zero communication. Combine that with shortened store hours. Terrible customer service.

reviews.text: It may be a smaller space but,the knowledge I walked out with was immense. We were given a tour by a very knowledgeable  guide who was able to tell much about early aviation. This was a great experience well worth the trip.
Absolutely great aviation environment. The volunteers here are very passionate and excited to teach anyone who walks through the door. Small hanger but beautiful aircraft and a time well spent here.
An amazing array of aircraft and awesome volunteers.  Fun atmosphere.

The airport is tiny, so we didn't know what to expect. We were pleasantly surprised by how many planes there were and the wealth of information they had on each airplane. The history of each plane was lovingly documented by their enthusiastic volunteers. In the summertime, they offer plane rides for a small fee.
Give yourself 1.5 to 2 hrs to climb on the planes and read all the materials provided. Volunteers provided lots of fun extra information and antidotes that added to the experience.
Just a few minutes drive from Hendersonville.
Def. Worth a visit. Very cool place with lots of planes to see up close. Well maintained and nice people who work here. Hours are tricky, so look it up before you go

recommendations.address: 36 W Jordan St, Brevard, NC 28712, USA

reviews.text:
This beautiful little studio is hidden away on a less-traveled street in downtown Brevard, along with at least 4 other small shops of equitable charm. The window display is tasteful and eye-catching, so I went in the other day to check it out, as I am a fan of screen printing and local art.

If you want a cute greeting or thank-you card, go here. If you need some art for your (or a friend's) home, go here. If you want a unique t-shirt with a clean print, go here! If you need that one last color of Gelly Roll for your pen collection, there are a TON of them here. If you like raccoons, hiking, flowers, trees, foxes, mushrooms, and nature in general, you'll love this store. There are even sketchbooks and screen printing supplies! I found a great Black Balsam print for a friend; and I will definitely be going back periodically to see what new items are released, as I was a big fan of the styles of artwork as well as their presentation. Shop small!
Beautiful art work

Starfangled is a really cute little shop with different kinds of prints and shirts and books and stickers. i want to decorate my home with everything in there! i bought a sticker for my car and it's hard to resist going back for more. their products are pretty good quality and hold up, and their shirts are super soft too. definitely worth stopping by to check this place out!!!

I absolutely love going to Starfangled! I’ve bought several unique prints and cards for myself and friends. I’ve also bought the coolest dino pillow, mountain tote, and nature artwork. I think one of the best aspects of this shop is seeing the owner actively working in the studio.
Love to see this, such a fun shop. Beautiful prints, fun pens.

reviews.text: Such a fun time mining for gems today! Our 4 girls, ages 8 to 15 loved it. Holden was super helpful and friendly. You could tell he loves his job and is super good at it! Lots of fun affordable things for the kids to pick out too!
Absolutely beautiful and enjoyable. There is so much to help calm one with a variety of colors and even fossils! One should definitely run by on their visit in town, it is a must.

My husband and I had never been gem mining before. We had friends come into town to visit that also had never been before so we took a chance. This place was AWESOME! Staff was super knowledgeable & friendly and the store was clean & well maintained. The GREEN BUCKET is the way to go!!! It was nice to act like a kid again! We will definitely be back as well as recommend to any friends that come to visit. Thanks Chris for a wonderful experience!
wonderful crystal shop and gem mine. they have such a wonderful abundant selection of their different gem types. i got a magical looking labradorite that is super high quality.

My husband and I had the BEST time at Crystal Mountain a few weeks ago! We purchased the big green bucket and were amazed by how many gemstones we got (not to mention a HUGE geode)! Unfortunately there was a bit of a mixup when we were checking out and our bags with our emeralds, rubies, and other gemstones was misplaced. I didn't realize this until we got home and called to see if it was still at the store. It wasn't, but they made up for it by sending us a box of dirt to mine for gemstones at home! They really went above and beyond and I highly recommend you check this place out. Prices are great, staff is fantastic - you won't be disappointed!

So it made it even more amazing when Adam was kind and helpful, even though we showed up right before they closed down for the night. He was well versed in the food and was an all around awesome guy. He made the wait for our food enjoyable with fantastic conversation and made the night better than expected.

Can't recommend highly enough. Everyone working is super cool and knowledgeable, the beer, of course, is amazing. Fun atmosphere for the whole family. Don't just visit if you're in town, this is a destination!
We both had an Omega Burger (salmon) and we highly recommend it. I always get it. The beer was fine as well.

Stopped here after hiking 3 waterfalls. I was Thirsty! They have a nice large covered patio with communal tables and outdoor games. A friendly atmosphere and quite a substantial beer selection. They had at least 20 beers on tap. We didn't try the food so I can't review that, but it did smell good. They support local musicians and the talent that day was fun to listen to.

reviews.text: Biking enthusiasts know this place. Is it the best bike shop in America? It's in the running. It's at the foot of one of the most unique trail systems in the country where rides are measured in hours, not by miles. If you have a part or a piece on your bike that needs fixing? Done. You need to upgrade one? Done. You need advice about life, love and politics? Sit down and have a beer. They've got plenty on tap. And dang good food trucks. If you're in the area, drop by, you won't regret it.
I brought in my Ebike to get the tires replaced and a few other small repairs. The guys there at the shop were very fast and did a fantastic job. It runs like a dream now. Thanks!
Super well stocked mtb destination. Great selection of camping and other outdoor gear too. Friendly and knowledgeable staff. Full service bike dept too. Also dogs and beer. 10/10

They have a very good selection. Busy shop. Good beer and bike brands. Good food trucks outside. Only reason for 4 stars is I couldn't get any help at all and had to find everything I was looking for. Would have bought some shoes but nobody would help me

reviews.text:
Came in from Florida looking to stop in for a beer and some food with our pups. Weather was a beautiful 52° and sunny at 1pm...we were told they were not opening the outdoor area because it was too cold... Really??

Found another Brewery just down the hill and enjoyed our outdoor seating and food right by the river...

We won't bother trying to come back. Do not recommend.

I was pretty disappointed compared to our experience last summer. None of the staff were wearing masks. The food was not as good. They are serving a Beyond burger for the meatless option not Impossible. (Like eating soybeans vs. a real burger)  Overall our 50+$ lunch was less than remarkable. Last year when we came I couldn’t wait to come back. No longer the case. Also few gluten free options.

This place is a hidden gem in a smaller town. We've been here 5 times or more, and it's consistently great food. You wouldn't think that a brewery could provide this type of quality, but they DO!! The salmon with the sweet onion sauce is my go to, although I've tried other things on the menu and I've never been disappointed. This place is on point! Great atmosphere too!!!

Super popular and busy restaurant serving a variety of craft beers brewed off site and nice selections from the food menu. It seems you need to be prepared for a good wait most times, I waited 45min on a Monday eve. Staff is very friendly, especially the table servers. The bar staff seems challenged to preform under very busy conditions. This is a pretty large venue with several inside rooms in addition to outside. Bar service slow, food arrived pretty timely though and was prepared very well.

Very good food and atmosphere. Try the honey sriracha honey wings. The Boojum burger was cooked just like I ask and was very flavorful.
Our server was spot on and attentive without being over bearing.
We each had a different beer and all were good.
Sorry, I forgot to take pics of the food since I was so excited to see my friend and her parents. We all happened to be in the area at the same time.

reviews.text: I don't leave reviews but the flavor was exquisite, the price was as cheap as any Mexican restaurant my wife and I have ever eaten at, they are super friendly, they love God and they don't serve booze! 4.6 stars, although the highest rated Mexican restaurant I've ever seen, is not high enough. We even ordered seconds which is also a forest for us. Btw we are from Iowa on vacation but this is a must if you like good food.

GUYS! Such a small privately owned place. So GREAT :) everyone was so nice and caring. We stumbled upon this place on Main Street and decided to give it a try. DO IT!!! Food was PHENOMENAL. So authentic ❣️

Couldn’t ask for any nicer owners. They genuinely care about their customers and provide great food and service, even when they are short handed. It is refreshing to hear praise music in English and Spanish!
The food is very good and always done right. They have a salsa bar and great service! The owner is so happy and personable and treats you like family. Nothing but good things to say about this place.

Some of the kindest restaurant experiences you can have in Brevard! Genuinely a wonderful place. Great food. They do not serve alcohol and haven't since they opened. A nice family atmosphere with an extensive menu.

reviews.text: Highly recommend! The food was delicious. Very quaint nice atmosphere!

We were in town visiting Brevard, NC this past weekend.  This restaurant was very close to where we were staying, talk about convenient.  That's where the good things ended.  We arrived with our party of 8 and were told by the first hostess, "we only seat tables of 6, sorry."  I replied, we can split our group up into 4 and 4, to which she said no sorry we can't do that.  What in the world?!?!  The couple who were sat outside enjoying their meal were as completely dumbfounded as we were.  We proceeded to walk away, when were met by their second hostess, after more confusion about seating, she explained she could seat us outside that they had room outside.  Then, as if she was steering us away from eating there she saw we had four children ages 9 to 13 and stated they did not have a kids menu.  She gave the menu to one of our kids, looking at him as if he wasn't going to like anything they served.  We had had enough at that point, and told them no thank you.  Never have I ever been to a place supposedly called the "Neighborhood Eatery" who was more inclined to dismiss a group of paying customers.  Whether the food was good or not, we'll never know, but the service was atrocious!

Thank you Chef Trey for amazing food! And cheers to the rest of the staff for wonderful service! We had a hard a time choosing a favorite...the gorgonzola gnocchi won....also highly recommend the  beet salad, artichokes, and the crab cake. We will be back!!
We had a party of four who dined at Vescovo last week, and we were not disappointed.  All of the entrees, two filets, a bone in pork chop, and a grouper special, were prepared to perfection.
Great food as always.  Excellent service as well !

reviews.text: Food was amazing and great selection of beer. Everyone was super hospitable but I want to shout out our server Chris. We were a big party and made sure we had attention and made great recommendations. The brewery is definitely something to see and one of a kind. Highly recommend!
Food was delicious. Recommend  house pizza and the burger. Server Chris was outstanding. Also recommend Wild Little Thing brew. Delicious. Don't let "Sour" fool you. It is not. Great time for family.
Service, excellent. Beer delicious varied. Grounds spectacular!  Food very good and reasonable. Well worth the trip. I wish much future success to the folks at SN!

I went to college in Chico in the early 1990's and had many great memories of their original brewery.   I couldn't wait to visit the Mills River location to see if they lived up to the Chico tradition.   They did not disappoint.   This place is amazing!!!!  Great food, beer and gift shop.   It's a must visit for Sierra Nevada fans.

Always a great selection of beers.  And of course the seasonal brews for this time of year are great.  The pretzels with beer cheese is a given. You can have a nice dinner and then go out back, order another beer, and sit by the large fire pit. Live music on the weekends. Convenient location close to the Asheville airport.

reviews.text: The parking was scant, side of the road-style parking. Fortunately, during the week, we had plenty of room to park. The hike was so incredibly short, I’d refer to it as a casual walk. It is an easy walk for anyone who wants to see a good waterfall, without a long or difficult hike. Really nice-looking waterfall, and I imagine during hotter weather, a dip in the pool at the bottom would be amazing.

Drove from Fort Mill, SC to the nearest waterfall which is Looking Glass waterfall. It’s about a 3 hour drive, which is a great day trip/weekend getaway. The first stop we went to was the waterfall which was just magnificent. The water directly under the fall is bone chilling my goodness! After leaving the waterfall, the sliding rock was next, which is a huge smooth rock with flowing water over it, that has been used as a water slide. The water is slightly warmer than the waterfall. My first experience at a waterfall was a success!

Looking Glass Falls is beautiful!

1.  No hiking required.  There is parking along the road and also a small parking area if you drive just past the falls.

2.  The area is very clean.

3.  You can see the falls from the street. There are steps and railing that lead you down to the water.  Once you reach the water you can walk out on huge rocks (careful, they are slippery) and even swim into and beneath the falls.

4.  It can be very crowded but it's a nice place for families and even kids (as long as you have pretty good mobility).

5.  The view is amazing.  There aren't really good areas to picnic or even just lounge around near the base of the falls.  You really just have to make room for yourself and your family and enjoy being in nature.

6.  Obviously, there are no bathrooms.  Use it before you come!

The most accessible and stunning waterfall in Pisgah! My wife & I have been a few times, our most recent visit she was 6 months pregnant and still climbing all over the rocks and enjoying the mist. Highly recommend visiting in the morning to beat the dense crowds, or on a cloudy day for the best photos. I’d love to see it frozen one day!

Great mountain swimming hole! The water is cold & so refreshing! It’s right off the main road and super easy to get to. The steps are manageable to get down to the base of the waterfall. If you go swimming, prepare yourself to acclimate to the rush of air that comes off the falls. You will need to practice your breathing before you jump in. Enjoy!

🥾ATTN: Hiking Boots or Water shoes are highly recommended. I grabbed a pair of Astral all purpose outdoor shoes from Davidson Outfitters at the intersection there in town. They worked perfectly, inside and outside of the water.

reviews.text: Driving from northern Virginia to Western North Carolina, the motor blew in my car. My wife and I had to make it home after the holiday. For the same price of renting a car and fuel, we were able to get a last minute flight from Avl to Iad. That puts us one exit away from our home. Its a cute, nice airport. The staff are very helpful. The jet was small, but very comfy. We flew United and made it home in an hr and a half for less than 600 for the both of us. That was purchased 3hrs before the flight. We will now fly here to visit family. I never knew there were regular flights from close to home to close to family for very low price, especially if booked in advance. We will now fly in and out of here every few months. Such a great experience

I was very pleased. Nice friendly staff. They were very helpful to my mom who needed wheelchair assistant. They made she she got on the plane on time and took really good care of her medical device. Thank you all so much.
Very convenient airport. Close to interstate exit, parking close to terminal. Minimal walking and getting luggage on return was quick.  Small tasteful food court.
We had no wait and were seated with coffee quickly. Our waiter was attentive and efficient. The food was wonderful and exactly as we ordered it.

Let me start by saying that the only reason we booked with this airport is because the flights were the earlier than Knoxville. This was all in vain since the scheduling is so poor with this airport. The departing and returning flights were both over 45 minutes late. Then, when we returned home we were stuck on the taxiway due to a plane being in the way since they were also late. We were stuck for over 30 minutes. We will never, ever fly out of this airport again if we don’t have to. The scheduling is poor and unreliable, and the facilities are cramped. McGee-Tyson is far superior and reliable.

Attended Pumpkinfest for the 2nd time. Loved it.  Very well done, Grandkids enjoyed it almost as much as me.  Unpaid Bill and the Bad Czechs were great in concert.  The scavenger hunt was fun and just enough of a challenge for the kids. Lots of NON scary Halloween fun.

reviews.text: Always a must stop when I'm in the area!

We will go back asap on another day trip. The service was amazing too! Well worth every penny and every minute leading up to it. Their sauces were wonderful too! Especially the vinegar western one. I even asked if they had a sister company here, which they don't. ☹️. True Carolina BBQ and truly a wonderful restaurant and atmosphere! I am 100% thankful that I found them on Google. 😋😋😋🤗💖 By the way, they had the cleanest and nicest restroom that I have ever seen.

In the middle of almost nowhere.  A brewery next door.  The meal and the people were great.  It was outstanding.  Two types of pork, beef and awesome Cole slaw.  Two people stuffed for $ 32.00 add in an $8.00 tip and I went home very happy. I will go back.  Pilot cove cabins nearby and very nice.  Great time.
AWESOME! Visited for lunch.  Clean throughout.  Staff pleasant and attentive. Food very good.  Will be back next time I’m in the area.

UPDATE 2021 so we've been ordering takeaway for about a year now due to the plague. Unfortunately these folks don't always pay attention,  when you call in they're not really listening. Almost each and every time that we go in there about every other week to pick up our order, there's something missing.

Even though we ask them to double check the order it's always something, extra sauce missing, ear of corn missing, coleslaw missing. I just don't understand why they can't pay a little bit more attention, slow down and understand what's being said on the telephone and then have some quality control process to make sure that they are putting what was ordered in the bag. We are dropping them down to three stars. The food is still good but the service suffers due to inattention.

-----_---

reviews.text: In addition to wonderful bakery temptations Blue Ridge is a fine lunch destination. They have earned the Blue Zones approval by offering healthy options. The turkey sandwich is made with real on site roasted turkey, not processed lunch meat. Besides sandwiches there are interesting salad choices. Indoor seating or take out, outdoor tables nearby.

We hired Blue Ridge Bakery to bake our wedding cake and cater appetizers for a wedding in October. We were extremely unsatisfied with the experience. The customer service provided by the manager was terrible. She was nothing but rude and accusatory before we even entered our complaint. The baker oversold her capabilities and our "sage green and gold drip cake" was called by a guest "Nickelodeon green Slime and orange." It was so far from what we requested, we refused to display it for the remainder of our guests out of embarrassment. The only saving grace in the matter was the owner of the bakery, Katina, who was sweet and apologetic. She refunded a portion of our money, which was appreciated but unfortunately that does not provide us a presentable cake for our wedding day. The appetizers were good, but please do go elsewhere for your wedding cake.
I am on vacation from Florida and stumbled across this bakery. I bought a couple cookies and a 5 layer bar. The Tahini Sesame Cookie was probably the best cookie I have ever eaten. So good!
We found this bakery while visiting Brevard, the Outrageous brownie is so delicious. We will definitely come back.

Always a fantastic experience whenever we come here. We spend a week near Brevard each summer and this is always a must stop spot. Their baked goods have a fantastic variety and are always fresh. Come early for the best selection, but they have plenty throughout most of the day. Honestly, we've never had anything bad here over the years so I can't recommend anything specific other than any dessert or breakfast item!

Always a special morning when we visit our Farmer's Market. Great vendors and great products.

reviews.text: Super friendly staff and great beer. I had no idea what to order so it was nice the employee let me try a few until I found one I loved. I was nervous they wouldn't do this due to covid but she wanted me to order one I liked. We sat outside by the heaters (in December) over looking the river. Great views, good people and delicious beer!

This has become one of the favorite breweries to visit in Asheville. Plenty of indoor/outdoor seating and room to move around. Pet friendly. Great selection of drafts that are made in house. They usually have a food truck on the property which makes it a one stop shop for all you need to have a good time.
Had the best experience when we went. We were treated like family. Joe was great! The view from the river was very relaxing. Definitely will visit again next time we are back in Ashville.

This is a must do while in Asheville! My husband and I love this place. We've done the tour a few times, sadly it's not being offered at the moment but hopefully they'll bring that back soon. After taking the tour we decided to go to Bruges, Belgium to visit the bar that started it all. We definitely wouldn't of known to go to such an incredible place without learning about New Belgium's history. The beer is delicious and very fairly priced. The staff is the absolute best! This brewery is unlike any other and it's in a great location that overlooks the French broad river. They also have food trucks that park out front in addition to a big lawn to chill on. Go check them out!!
Beautiful place to have some beers and chill. Right on the river, just beautiful. Beer was fresh and delicious. People were wonderful. Highly recommend.

reviews.text: Really good beer. Food was awesome too. Service was fantastic, we had a group that came in staggered over several hours, our waitress didn’t miss a beat. By the time we were done ordering food our app had already come out, due to a nice computer ordering thing the waitress had. Really nice patio. Recommend highly.

Peach was our server, and she was amazing.  She kept us and our dog in beer and water (our dog didn't have any beer),and she recommended avocados on my BLT. Let's talk about the BLT. It was the best I've ever had in my life. The bread is something called milk bread, the bacon is a thick cut sugar cure that should be patented, thick slices of tomatoes and Dukes mayo. To die for. My husband got the spicy fried chicken sandwich, which he loved, but it was a little too hot for him. I probably would have been fine with it. Also, its not on the menu,  but they will make a doggie chicken burger for $5.00. Also great beer, and a lovely outdoor seating area.

Update (3/2/2021) maybe I was I was here on a bad night previously because this place is rad. Great servers and great beer, and a good atmosphere.  They have expanded a ton and have a lot of outdoor space, much of it with heaters.  Definitely a go-to when I'm in town!

Original review (a while ago) Pretend like you don’t care and they might serve you. The beer is delicious and well done. However they don’t care about you as a patron. You’ll wait forever and then they will show that they’re not in a hurry. I sat on the patio and apparently never made eye contact with the “servers” out there.

Great spot! It’s a bit of a short hike from downtown, so wear comfy shoes if you’re walking over. There are numerous seating areas with different feels. Indoor/out, shady, etc. service was solid. The group loved the pretzels (beware the very spicy grainy mustard!), BLT, and burgers/chips. Sangria and flights are on point. Looks like a great event space too!

Loved this place. My wife and I took our dog with us and it was great. Good food and beer. Not a lot of traditional beers. This is the place if you really want to try some eccentric funky beers. A lot of sours. Great atmosphere. It got cooler in the evening but we had a really cool table heater over us that made it incredibly comfortable. Very dog friendly and the food was good too.

Waited outside and TWENTY minutes later they brought my food, milk and the bill. They wanted me to pay $2.10 for the milk. I told them I tried to pay 20 minutes ago and no one came back out and I didn't want to wait any longer for my change. He sarcastically told me to have a good day. I should have told him to take it out of the tip I left. I waited 1 hour and 20 minutes for my food. You can knock off 2 bucks.

If Google allowed 10 stars this place would get it. We stopped in on a Saturday around lunch time with our dog. We were immediately sat at the quiet end of the patio which we were very happy about. We were greeted warmly by what I assume was the manager, a runner and a server. They were having some special appetizers that were up our alley. We had the southern fondue, the pork cracklings and cheese plate with flambe peaches. It was all to die for. Midway through our meal a storm started to roll in. The manager came out and made us aware of the situation and moved us immediately under the covered area of the patio before the storm hit with plenty of time to spare. The service was second to none and we will absolutely be back our next visit to town.

When our guests ask for a recommendation for a local restaurant, The Square Root is always at the top of our list. They have been serving consistently great meals for years. They have outdoor seating and they have curbside pickup. They have the prettiest bar in town, made from a natural slab of wood. Great local ambience, friendly staff, beautiful decor, and a great attitude. And the food is amazing!

Experienced lunch here today with my wife. She had the grilled chicken sandwich with mixed vegetables and I had the London Broil on a Hoagie with pasta salad. We both agreed that we would have the sandwich but differ on our sides. The mixed vegetables were a flavor delight. As for the Pasta Salad, it was mayonnaise based and had little to nothing special for the palette. Of course that was my preference.  Other that love Mayo may love it. I prefer the Italian Dressing base.

reviews.text: So I had my doubts about this place but my friends wanted to try it.  It's a bagel sandwich steamed, and it did not disappoint.   Had the Italian on an everything bagel.  The steam seemed to just meld all the flavors together.  It was really good, oh and a bit messy, so what, it was yum!  I will return when in the area.

Kinda conflicted, because the staff is very friendly and the food was pretty decent, but I’ve never ordered a bagel from anywhere ever that somehow came out piping hot, yet not toasted in the slightest. I understand the uniqueness of the steaming process that they have here, but it seems that it negates the whole point of what makes a bagel a bagel, both flavor and texture-wise. It might be a little bit of a petty perspective on my end, but I feel like not toasting a bagel, especially for $6-8+ sandwiches from a place where the whole bit IS the bagel, is a little odd, especially for a breakfast sandwich, and definitely prevents it from being the solid comfort food it could be. I would still recommend trying it at least once, though, since it IS a unique preparation and might be someone else’s “cup of tea” more so than my own.

Today was my first time ever eating here. My experience was awesome from the customer service experience to the amazing food. Visiting from out of town but I will definitely come back to eat again my next visit to the area.

reviews.text: Ended up at Maya's on a whim because the restaurant we were going to was closed. Whole group had a delightful experience! Food far exceeded expectations with good portion sizes. reviews.text: At 16:30 we sat down for our enjoyment ... We consulted with the bartender who was very kind and welcoming and ordered two tasting trays. In each tray 4 small delicious dishes that add up to a glass of beer. The fish and chips were great and the atmosphere was fun. we had a lot of fun. Mimi from Israel

My husband and I visited Wicked Weed during our honeymoon and were so impressed by the beer and the service. All of the beer was delicious! We also had a fantastic waiter who was so attentive and absolutely wonderful overall. He asked us about the types of beer we like and then brought us different samples he recommended. We definitely ended up buying more beer from the beer store than we originally planned because of him, but we have no regrets! I wish I could remember his name, but he was there the afternoon of August 31st and he knew the scientific name of my leg tattoo. He deserves a bonus!

Fantastic place. I loved the atmosphere, and the selection for what was expected was well above par.  For a Saturday night, the lines were not terrible, I may have waited 5 minutes tops to get my beer. The people I met there were awesome, and super friendly. Only reason for deducting a star is due to lack of seating, otherwise great.

We had a great time! We had the local flight, which showed of a few of the taproom-only beers. We also had the fish and chips, which were really impressive. The fish was good, and the fries were GREAT! Our bartender Matt also helped us decide between a few of the other good nearby breweries. This was a great experience, and we'll definitely be back the next time we're in town.

My wife and I were in Ashville for just a couple of days, so picking out of so many places was hard. Wicked Weed was not a mistake! They have a great variety of beers that accommodate all types of beer drinkers. To make it better, they have a great atmosphere to accompany their beers and sell many of their beers they have on tap to take home! Personal preference for me is for pub style breweries to have a little more imagination on the burger front, and the fries are crispy, but again lacking in imagination. My only reason for rating it 4 stars. Will definitely come back when in town again!

We love the name of your coffee shop! The pastries were delicious and the coffee too! We will be back! Everyone working was pleasant and joyful too which we look for in a restaurant or coffee shop! God bless your business.

The coffee was amazing (she had a bear claw latte and enjoyed it every morning we were there!) and the service staff were so friendly! So good we bought a bag to make some at home. But we still love to visit from time to time❤️
